{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|おれ}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=おれ|-}}. Found in use mostly from ancient times until roughly the {{w|Heian period}},<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref> used to refer in the {{l|en|second person}} to social {{l|en|inferior}}s or to {{l|en|insult}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref><ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref>

The {{l|en|second person}} sense of {{m|en|you}} appears to be obsolete in modern Japanese.

Not to be confused with the modern term {{m|ja|俺|tr=ore}} with the {{l|en|first person}} sense of {{m|en|I}}, {{m|en|me}}. See {{m|ja|俺}} for that sense.

